│ The most direct and robust way to fix this is to make `InstructionsState::valid()` itself safer. I will modify it to check if the `VF` member is valid before trying to use it. A        │
│ default-constructed `VectorizationFactor` has a `Min` value of 0. I can use this to detect if `VF` is uninitialized.                                                                     │
